Let’s first learn the Bassoon fingering diagram.  It’s broken into
four sections, left fingers, left thumb, right fingers and right
thumb.
Let's look at our first note, C.

They’re called Ledger Lines and they allow us to have notes that are lower or higher than the staff.  This low C is on a Ledger
Line below the staff.
So now lets try playing C.
For our first exercises we are going to practice playing C and rests.
For every exercise you'll get a "count in" which is one measure of tick sounds. These ticks are called the Metronome.  Begin playing after 4 beats.  Play with the Metronome as best you can.

Play through all the exercises then try the challenge!  The challenge will give
you a new exercise each time you play it.  You can change the length and tempo
in the settings menu.
